              <PROPTEXT offset="1049"> you might be able to physically clear drugs from a person's system with the aid of a solid door and a deadlock, but what are the emotional consequences of forcing them to endure an involuntary and painful drug withdrawal, without being psychologically prepared, or even willing, to do so?    Has Watters considered what would happen once they were released? People use drugs to block out painful underlying problems, and those problems won't dissolve after a mandatory drying-out period.</PROPTEXT>
